<h2>The Challenge</h2>
<p>The sinking of the Titanic is one of the most infamous shipwrecks in his=
tory.</p>
<p>On April 15, 1912, during her maiden voyage, the widely considered =E2=
=80=9Cunsinkable=E2=80=9D RMS Titanic sank after colliding with an iceberg.=
 Unfortunately, there weren=E2=80=99t enough lifeboats for everyone onboard=
, resulting in the death of 1502 out of 2224 passengers and crew.</p>
<p>While there was some element of luck involved in surviving, it seems som=
e groups of people were more likely to survive than others.</p>
<p>In this challenge, we ask you to build a predictive model that answers t=
he question: =E2=80=9Cwhat sorts of people were more likely to survive?=E2=
=80=9D using passenger data (ie name, age, gender, socio-economic class, et=
c).</p>
